_prev_prog_2.Description:
Coatex complies with the prevention program level 2 requirements and have implemented best practices consistent with industry standards.  This program is organized into the following elements: 

1) Safety Information is maintained on aqueous ammonia hazards and the aqueous ammonia system; 

2) Hazard Review/PHA of the system was conducted and has been periodically reviewed to ensure adequacy of controls; 

3) Operating and Maintenance procedures provide operators and maintenance staff the information necessary to safely operate and maintain the system; 

4) Training is provided for operators and maintenance personnel; 

5) Contractors working on or near the system are selected for safety performance, and are briefed on hazards and safety requirements of the job; 

6) Compliance Audits are conducted every three years to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives; 

7) Incident investigations are conducted for incidents involving ammonia releases and near misses that endanger employees or the public.
